		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Cartoon characters at the side is a nice solution to the narrow play area caused by a sprite-based playfield. It worked for <em>Dr. Mario</em> to hide the fact that its playfield is likewise 64 pixels wide. But who administers the sync rights to &quot;Blurred Lines&quot;?

		

